parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spark plug separation can cause engine misfires, poor engine performance, and decreased fuel efficiency, which can lead to reduced vehicle safety and performance.
symptoms: Engine misfires
poor engine performance
decreased fuel efficiency
spark plugs separating from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The interference between the brake pedal and gas pedal can cause unintended acceleration, loss of braking ability, or difficulty stopping the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal and gas pedal stick together
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the gas pedal is difficult to press
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle is difficult to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause difficulty in steering, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel is hard to turn
the steering wheel makes abnormal noises
the steering wheel feels tight or stiff
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating and failure of the defroster can cause reduced visibility, especially during inclement weather, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The defroster blows warm or hot air
the defroster stops working
the defroster makes a loud or unusual noise
the windshield or windows fog up or ice up excessively
the defroster's electrical components or wiring show signs of overheating or damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stickiness of the clutch pedal can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-miss incidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels sticky or grabby
the clutch pedal does not release smoothly
the clutch pedal requires excessive force to release
the clutch pedal vibrates or pulses when pressed.
